article.description: Tramaine Isabell scored 23 points and Kurk Lee sank the winning 3-pointer to lift Drexel to a 72-71 win over Quinnipiac on Monday night.
article.headline: Drexel edges Quinnipiac 72-71 on Lee's late 3
article.linkText: Drexel edges Quinnipiac 72-71 on Lee's late 3
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Tramaine Isabell scored 23 points and Kurk Lee sank the winning 3-pointer to lift Drexel to a 72-71 win over Quinnipiac on Monday night. Drexel (6-6) led most of the second half but Quinnipiac stayed close, getting a pair of free throws from Cameron Young with 34 seconds left to trim the gap to 69-68 and then edging into the lead moments later when Isaiah Washington dropped in a layup. Rich Kelly stretched it to 71-69 on a free throw before Drexel got the ball to Lee at the other end for the winning 3-pointer with two seconds left. Kelly missed a 3 at the buzzer. Lee and Alihan Demir finished with 14 points apiece and Sammy Mojica had 13 for Drexel, which outrebounded the Bobcats 46-28. Young led Quinnipiac (3-8) with 24 points and Abdulai Bundu added 17 points.
